quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  8,53,"This is because Allah would never change the blessings He has bestowed upon a people until they change their own attitude and conduct. Indeed, Allah is All-Hearing, All-Knowing.",""
  8,54,"Their case is like the people of Pharaoh and those who came before them. They rejected the signs of their Lord, so We destroyed them<sup>31</sup> for their sins and drowned the people of Pharaoh; they were all wrongdoers.","[31] Repetition of the example of the earlier nations is to emphasize the inevitable fate of those who disbelieve or disobey Allah."
  8,55,"The worst of moving creatures<sup>32</sup> before Allah are those who persist in disbelief, so they do not believe,","[32] See 8:22-23."
  8,56,"those with whom you [O Prophet] made a treaty, but they break their treaty every time, and they do not fear Allah.",""
  8,57,"If you encounter them in battle, make a fearsome example of them<sup>33</sup> for those who are behind them, so that they may be deterred.","[33] i.e., Treat the treacherous who betray their pledges with due severity."
  8,58,"If you fear betrayal from any people, throw their treaty back at them openly<sup>34</sup>, for Allah does not like the treacherous.","[34] i.e., announce to them its dissolution so that you both be on the same footing."
  8,59,"The disbelievers should not think that they are unreachable; they cannot escape.",""
  8,60,"Prepare against them whatever force<sup>35</sup> you can and cavalry, to deter Allahâ€™s enemies and your enemies<sup>36</sup>, and others besides them whom you do not know<sup>37</sup>, but Allah knows them. Whatever you spend<sup>38</sup> in the cause of Allah will be repaid to you in full, and you will not be wronged.","[35] All types of power: physical, mental as well as weapons. [36] To make them think twice before invading or fighting them.\n [37] i.e., lurking enemies.\n [38] Funds are necessary for preparing the force."
  8,61,"If they incline to peace, then incline to it, and put your trust in Allah, for He is the All-Hearing, the All-Knowing.",""
